    <section class="" id="designer">
        <figure class="cover">
            <figcaption>Designer</figcaption>
            <img src="/img/about-wireframes-l.jpg" alt="" />
            <!-- <img src="/img/about-books-1.0-m.jpg" alt="">
		<img src="/img/about-workshopmess-bw-m.jpg" alt=""> -->
        </figure>
        <div class="container">
            <h2>Design & Product Leader</h2>
            <p>I deeply believe that putting people at the center of everything you do - as a leader, as a designer, as an entrpreneur - leads to good work and good business outcomes.</p>

        <p>Most recently I led Enterprise product design at <img src="/img/disney-logo.svg" width="100px" style="margin-bottom: -.5em;" alt="Disney"> for our streaming services <a href="https://www.disneyplus.com">Disney+</a>, <a href="https://www.hulu.com">Hulu</a>, <a href="https://www.starplus.com">STAR+</a>, and <a href="https://espnplus.com">ESPN+</a>. Previously I led design for Growth (propelling Disney+ & ESPN+ to 130M subscribers in 2 years!), UX Research and Sports Products. Before joining Disney, I built high performing teams at startups, and enterprises using a customer-first mindset and cross-functional collaboration.</p>

        <p>My leadership approach is based on my core values of <b>curiosity</b> and <b>authenticity</b>. I have also been told that I excel at inspirational leadership and product strategy; but the work I’m most proud of is expanding design’s business impact and mentoring design leaders.</p>

        </div>
    </section>
    <section class="" id="cycling">
        <figure class="cover">
            <img src="/img/kankamagus.jpg" alt="">
            <figcaption>Cyclist</figcaption>
        </figure>
        <div class="container fade slide" data-spy="scroll">
            <h2>Cyclist</h2>
            <h3 class="">FTP: 3.5w/kg</h3>
            <p>My happy place is riding my bike across the New England countryside; on road and off. It is a source of physical and psychological nourishment for me. I try ride about 160km or 6 hrs a week.</p>
            <p>In August 2023, I toured across the Green Mountains of Vermont – riding 420km (260mi) over four days.</p>
            <p><iframe id="strava-rides" frameborder='0' allowtransparency='true' scrolling='no' title="BMC Strava Feed"></iframe></p>
            <script type="text/javascript">
            window.addEventListener('load', function() {
                var stravaRides = 'https://www.strava.com/athletes/773650/latest-rides/69a2b8f6090a8e92b3ea1c24ae6bbccdc629077e';
                document.getElementById('strava-rides').src = stravaRides;
            }, false);
            </script>
    </section>
